##  Directory Enumeration (Gobuster)

### Objective  
To discover hidden directories and API endpoints on a web application.

### Tool Used  
- Gobuster

### Command Used  
gobuster dir -u http://localhost:3000 -w common.txt --exclude-length 75002

### Key Findings  
- Discovered multiple endpoints including:
  - /assets
  - /rest
  - /api
  - /robots.txt
  - /.well-known/security.txt  

- Some endpoints returned **500 Internal Server Error**, indicating backend processing issues.

### Security Insight  
- Hidden endpoints increase the attack surface  
- API routes (/rest, /api) are critical and often targeted  
- 500 errors may reveal backend weaknesses  

### Skills Demonstrated  
- Directory enumeration  
- Handling false positives (response filtering)  
- Identifying high-value endpoints  
